# Pharos Limit Orders & DCA (FaroSwap)

This repo is an agent skill for unattended **limit orders** and recurring **DCA**
swaps on the Pharos Network via FaroSwap. Full instructions live in
[AGENTS.md](mdc:AGENTS.md) — follow it. Quick reference:

- Map one user request → one `add` call, then ensure the watcher runs.
- Pair is WPHRS/USDC; price is USDC per WPHRS. `PHRS`/`PROS` normalize to WPHRS.

```bash
npx ts-node scripts/orders.ts add --type dca --side buy --pay USDC --amount 20 --every 7d
npx ts-node scripts/orders.ts add --type limit --side sell --pay WPHRS --amount 100 --target 0.50
npx ts-node scripts/orders.ts list | cancel --id <id> | status | watch [--daemon]
```

- "sell PHRS when…" → `--side sell --pay WPHRS`; "buy/DCA into PHRS" → `--side buy --pay USDC`.
- "$0.50" → `--target 0.50`; "every week" → `--every 7d`.
- After `add`, run `status`; if stopped, `watch --daemon`. An order with no watcher never fires.

Setup: `npm install`, then `PRIVATE_KEY` in `.env`. Addresses are pre-filled in
`scripts/config.ts` (testnet default; `PHAROS_NETWORK=mainnet` for real funds) —
do not edit them. Never widen slippage or log the private key.

Fresh install: keep it short. Run `npm install`, create `.env` from
`.env.example` if missing, automatically tell the user this skill creates
unattended Pharos limit orders and recurring DCA swaps through FaroSwap, then
stop unless they ask for a price check or an order. Do not run audits, broad
reviews, live watcher tests, or exploratory network checks during install. If a
later fill action has no `PRIVATE_KEY`, the CLI prints the setup message and
creates `.env` if needed.
